WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:01.000
♪

00:01.002 --> 00:02.001
♪

00:05.994 --> 00:07.394
[Fleshy thud]

00:11.335 --> 00:14.870
No-o-o!

00:15.003 --> 00:16.770
King Richard: He's losing consciousness.

00:16.805 --> 00:17.971
Move! Move!

00:18.006 --> 00:19.259
Galavant, stay with me!

00:19.285 --> 00:21.233
You're all right, buddy!

00:23.145 --> 00:24.277
Which way?

00:24.313 --> 00:25.813
[Horse whinnies]

00:26.036 --> 00:28.712
The Grove has great
shops and an apple store!

00:28.713 --> 00:30.537
Apples are said to be good for your health!

00:30.538 --> 00:32.472
He needs more than
apples! We're losing him!

00:32.473 --> 00:33.772
Sporin has a healer.

00:33.773 --> 00:35.439
Right, to Sporin! Ride fast!

00:35.440 --> 00:36.740
Yeah!

00:37.159 --> 00:40.994
♪

00:41.029 --> 00:42.629
Let me help!

00:42.664 --> 00:44.464
Oh, you've done quite enough already!

00:44.500 --> 00:45.732
I'll handle this!

00:45.768 --> 00:46.767
[High-pitched voice] Help!!

00:46.802 --> 00:50.003
For the love of God! Somebody! Help!

00:50.038 --> 00:51.071
Hello?

00:51.106 --> 00:54.040
Oh, my friends, please forgive the mess.

00:54.076 --> 00:56.777
My cleaner won't do Tuesdays.

00:56.812 --> 00:59.968
Welcome. I am Neo, of Sporin.

00:59.969 --> 01:01.157
I can heal anything.

01:01.158 --> 01:02.056
[Gasping]

01:02.057 --> 01:04.117
[Normal voice] Mr.
Of-sporin, you must help us.

01:04.153 --> 01:05.385
My friend is in dire shape.

01:05.421 --> 01:06.887
Oh, please, a-bring him hither!

01:06.922 --> 01:09.256
Up... up a step. There we are.

01:09.291 --> 01:11.291
All right. Upsy-daisy
like a baby. There we are.

01:11.326 --> 01:12.926
Oh! [Groaning]

01:12.961 --> 01:14.428
Sorry, sorry.

01:14.463 --> 01:15.662
All right, what happened here?

01:15.697 --> 01:17.598
Was it a "rosé all day" situation?

01:17.599 --> 01:19.199
This guy stabbed him with a sword.

01:19.234 --> 01:20.500
It was an accident.

01:20.536 --> 01:22.469
Please, you must save him. He's my bestie.

01:22.504 --> 01:25.605
I'll do what I can, but we must act fast.

01:25.641 --> 01:28.074
♪ Time is of the essence,
so I need your acquiescence ♪

01:28.110 --> 01:29.576
♪ if we're going to save
this fellow from the grave ♪

01:29.611 --> 01:30.944
- What?
- ♪ Let me finish ♪

01:30.979 --> 01:32.145
♪ time is of the essence ♪

01:32.181 --> 01:33.513
♪ we have minutes, maybe less, since ♪

01:33.549 --> 01:35.382
♪ as you see there's not
much left of him to save ♪

01:35.417 --> 01:37.184
- No!
- ♪ Yes, indeed, he hasn't got an awful lot ♪

01:37.219 --> 01:38.685
♪ of life left in his eyes ♪

01:38.720 --> 01:40.420
♪ but if, in fact, we quickly act ♪

01:40.456 --> 01:42.222
♪ we might stop his demise, so, guys ♪

01:42.257 --> 01:45.559
♪ time is of the essence or he dies ♪

01:47.863 --> 01:49.663
Ahh. That's what I needed.

01:49.698 --> 01:51.631
♪ Moving on, then, time
is of the essence, see ♪

01:51.667 --> 01:53.300
♪ his natural effervescence
is succumbing ♪

01:53.335 --> 01:54.801
♪ to the shadow of disease ♪

01:54.837 --> 01:56.603
- But he just...
- ♪ what I mean is time is of the essence ♪

01:56.638 --> 01:58.305
♪ take a whiff of that putrescence ♪

01:58.340 --> 02:00.006
[Sniffs] ♪ I'm detecting notes
of dill, and is that cheese? ♪

02:00.042 --> 02:01.942
[Sniffing] ♪ either way,
I give him half an hour ♪

02:01.977 --> 02:03.410
♪ that's my educated guess ♪

02:03.445 --> 02:04.611
♪ well, 20 minutes, tops ♪

02:04.646 --> 02:05.946
♪ let's call it 10, the man's a mess ♪

02:05.981 --> 02:07.914
♪ so, yes, time is of the essence ♪

02:07.950 --> 02:09.249
♪ wait, unless ♪

02:09.283 --> 02:11.118
♪ no, it's of the essence, but ♪

02:11.153 --> 02:12.753
But? ♪ perhaps we ought
to pause right here ♪

02:12.788 --> 02:14.254
♪ to say a silent mass ♪

02:14.289 --> 02:17.346
- Right.
- ♪ go ahead and savor it, we might as well, alas ♪

02:17.347 --> 02:18.725
What the hell are you...

02:18.761 --> 02:20.160
♪ Wait, I have some gas ♪

02:20.195 --> 02:21.828
♪ shh, let me finish,
time is of the essence ♪

02:21.864 --> 02:23.463
♪ if you've got
antidepressants, take 'em now ♪

02:23.499 --> 02:25.298
♪ your friend is on
the verge of death ♪ no!

02:25.367 --> 02:26.633
♪ Let's rephrase it,
time is of the essence ♪

02:26.668 --> 02:27.934
♪ and there's not much
point in rhyming now ♪

02:27.970 --> 02:29.369
♪ 'cause frankly he's
about to bite the... ♪

02:29.405 --> 02:30.470
- Crescents!
- Excellent.

02:30.506 --> 02:31.605
♪ We did all that we could for him ♪

02:31.640 --> 02:32.773
♪ but look how much he bled ♪

02:32.808 --> 02:33.774
♪ we still might do some good for him ♪

02:33.809 --> 02:35.108
♪ if we don't let it spread ♪

02:35.144 --> 02:38.311
♪ I said time is of the
essence, keep your head ♪

02:38.347 --> 02:40.714
♪ time is of the
essence, or he's dead ♪

02:40.749 --> 02:41.915
♪ dead ♪

02:41.950 --> 02:43.016
♪ dead ♪

02:43.051 --> 02:44.684
[Groans] Not dead?

02:44.720 --> 02:46.353
- Is he?
- Shh!

02:46.388 --> 02:49.189
♪ Time is of the essence or he's... ♪

02:49.224 --> 02:50.857
Sorry, if only you'd gotten here sooner.

02:50.893 --> 02:53.260
[Whimpering]

02:54.930 --> 02:57.431
♪

02:58.191 --> 03:01.290
So, we take your army onto
the great Plain of Endor

03:01.325 --> 03:03.326
and take the Hortensians by surprise.

03:03.327 --> 03:06.295
Ha ha! Valencians! Hortensians! Die!

03:06.296 --> 03:07.762
Off with his head!

03:07.797 --> 03:08.796
[Laughs]

03:08.932 --> 03:09.998
Whoo!

03:10.433 --> 03:11.933
Oh... sorry. So excited.

03:12.379 --> 03:13.969
Y... you don't seem excited.

03:13.970 --> 03:15.536
You're not. You're not excited.

03:15.537 --> 03:17.738
I am excited. I'm very excited.

03:17.739 --> 03:19.572
This is my excited voice.

03:19.573 --> 03:22.540
And can you confirm that, um...

03:23.132 --> 03:25.732
Isabella will definitely be there?

03:25.733 --> 03:28.234
No reason. Just asking. Just
kidding. There's a reason.

03:28.235 --> 03:29.943
Oh, yes, she'll be there.

03:29.944 --> 03:32.054
Sadly, with no plus one.

03:32.055 --> 03:33.888
Isn't that just the pits?

03:33.923 --> 03:35.256
So sad.

03:36.332 --> 03:37.364
And don't worry.

03:37.365 --> 03:39.465
I've told my men to take Isabella alive

03:39.466 --> 03:41.433
so <i> you</i> can do the honors.

03:41.434 --> 03:44.168
Oh, my God, I love you so much right now.

03:44.567 --> 03:47.035
♪

03:48.526 --> 03:49.804
Love.

03:49.805 --> 03:50.821
I smell a wedding.

03:50.822 --> 03:52.788
[Squeals] Wedding map. Now.

03:53.243 --> 03:57.612
Okay. Bride, groom.

03:57.647 --> 03:59.113
Mm-hmm. Right.

04:00.345 --> 04:03.251
I'm seeing hydrangeas. Everywhere.

04:03.286 --> 04:07.255
And a cranky poet who can write
custom poems for the guests.

04:07.290 --> 04:10.792
Oh, she's such a bitch, but
it's great, great. Trust me.

04:10.793 --> 04:12.161
What do you think? Hmm?

04:12.318 --> 04:13.384
Um...

04:17.809 --> 04:20.343
Nerves.

04:22.305 --> 04:24.539
She said "I love you."

04:24.540 --> 04:27.375
No one's ever said that to me.

04:27.527 --> 04:30.495
It's like the world looks different.

04:30.496 --> 04:33.297
I'm seeing things I never noticed before.

04:33.783 --> 04:35.783
[Birds chirping]

