06:01.654 --> 06:03.771
Oh, Gareth, you're smiling.

06:04.950 --> 06:06.683
Sorry, could you stop it?

06:06.684 --> 06:08.817
I just find it deeply uns... settling.

06:08.818 --> 06:12.052
[Bubbling]

06:12.053 --> 06:13.619
I just can't believe he's dead.

06:13.620 --> 06:16.042
Does seem awfully early in the
season for something like this.

06:16.043 --> 06:17.309
Could he be mostly dead?

06:17.310 --> 06:19.811
But not all dead, 'cause
mostly dead is slightly alive?

06:20.737 --> 06:22.003
Yeah, that's not a thing.

06:22.859 --> 06:25.126
Well, I'm sorry, but you sang too long.

06:25.162 --> 06:26.528
Yeah, well, you stabbed him first.

06:26.563 --> 06:27.896
Is there anything else you can do?

06:28.858 --> 06:30.231
There is a potion

06:30.232 --> 06:31.757
for reviving the dead

06:32.127 --> 06:33.503
that I've been working on.

06:33.504 --> 06:35.604
But I've been missing one rare ingredient,

06:35.605 --> 06:37.161
so it's never been fully successful.

06:37.162 --> 06:38.840
What is this ingredient?

06:38.875 --> 06:42.477
I will climb any mountain,
battle any foe, slay any beast!

06:42.512 --> 06:45.280
A gray hair from the
beard of a middle-aged man

06:45.315 --> 06:49.083
who is pure of body, untouched by a woman.

06:49.949 --> 06:51.719
Rest in peace, my friend. I shall miss you.

06:51.755 --> 06:53.821
- Didn't I hear that you...
- You heard nothing!

06:53.857 --> 06:55.957
Where can we possibly find
a bearded middle-aged man

06:55.992 --> 06:57.892
who hasn't been touched by a woman.

06:58.346 --> 06:59.245
Spain?

06:59.485 --> 07:00.755
Who knows?

07:00.886 --> 07:02.665
To be honest, the chances
of finding that are

07:02.666 --> 07:04.566
as rare as that unicorn.

07:04.567 --> 07:06.433
Guys, look, there's a real, live unicorn

07:06.434 --> 07:08.000
looking in the window at us right now.

07:09.301 --> 07:10.700
[Unicorn snorts]

07:11.527 --> 07:12.073
Shoo.

07:12.108 --> 07:14.542
Unicorns are only attracted
by those untouched by...

07:14.578 --> 07:15.978
Get away.

07:20.403 --> 07:22.951
[Sighs] Fine, I'll donate
the damn beard hair.

07:22.986 --> 07:25.553
Gentle creature, if I live 1,000 years,

07:25.589 --> 07:29.190
I will never forget the day I
laid eyes on the likes of you.

07:29.226 --> 07:30.592
And the unicorn's cool, too.

07:31.795 --> 07:33.895
Hey, you don't have to be embarrassed.

07:33.930 --> 07:35.863
Honestly, Bobby, I...

07:35.899 --> 07:38.166
I've just always felt
that something that special

07:38.201 --> 07:41.302
should be shared with
someone you love, and...

07:41.338 --> 07:43.271
I've never been in love.

07:43.557 --> 07:44.731
Well, not yet.

07:44.732 --> 07:46.025
There's still time.

07:46.664 --> 07:47.503
Ow!

07:47.504 --> 07:48.736
Thank you.

07:49.755 --> 07:52.042
Four syllables, and it goes like this.

07:52.043 --> 07:53.710
[Makes airplane noises]

07:53.817 --> 07:55.541
So like an albatross...

07:55.542 --> 07:57.452
We just got a save-the-date from wormwood.

07:57.487 --> 07:59.120
Shh-shh. We're playing a new game.

07:59.155 --> 08:01.589
It's called "Guess the
future." And who cares?

08:01.625 --> 08:03.224
The wedding's been called off anyway.

08:03.260 --> 08:05.860
It's not for a wedding. It's for a war!

08:05.895 --> 08:08.496
Wormwood is in Valencia,
and they plan to invade us

08:08.531 --> 08:11.132
on Sunday, January 31st, 8:00 P.M. eastern.

08:11.167 --> 08:12.800
Set your DVR.

08:12.836 --> 08:15.169
"DVR"? What does that even mean?

08:15.205 --> 08:17.105
Just trying to play the
"Guess the future" game.

08:17.140 --> 08:19.674
Wait, he sent a save-the-date for a war?

08:19.709 --> 08:21.376
Who does such a thing?

08:22.912 --> 08:25.179
For real, Barry?

08:25.215 --> 08:27.482
You sent out save-the-date invitations

08:27.517 --> 08:29.250
to the people we are surprise attacking?!

08:30.300 --> 08:32.066
There are two lists! Two!

08:32.278 --> 08:35.245
Save-the-date for the wedding,
and save-the-date for the war!

08:35.246 --> 08:37.356
Not that difficult.

08:37.357 --> 08:40.061
Maybe if you stopped yelling
and took the time to teach.

08:40.096 --> 08:43.280
And who knows what they
mean by "light refreshments."

08:43.282 --> 08:45.133
So, what do we do here?

08:45.661 --> 08:48.202
Call for a war council? Sound an alarm?

08:49.769 --> 08:52.740
Wait, what's happening?
Why is everyone doing that?

08:53.171 --> 08:54.825
Hortensian tradition.

08:54.861 --> 08:56.961
In time of war, the last
person to put their finger

08:56.996 --> 08:58.930
next to their nose leads the troops.

09:00.733 --> 09:03.501
Uh... oh, darn!

09:03.536 --> 09:04.569
Dad!

09:04.604 --> 09:06.737
I'm sorry, Bunny. I suck at war.

09:06.773 --> 09:09.307
That's why our kingdom was taken
by Richard in the first place.

09:09.342 --> 09:11.809
[Chuckling] Well, don't look at me!

09:11.844 --> 09:13.744
I don't know anything about leading troops.

09:13.780 --> 09:16.914
I mean, one-on-one combat, yes, but armies?

09:16.950 --> 09:18.916
And I've finally got
the chance to just relax

09:18.952 --> 09:20.084
and have some "me" time.

09:20.119 --> 09:21.252
You encouraged that, Mom.

09:21.287 --> 09:23.154
Well, maybe you can do both.

09:23.189 --> 09:24.789
Oh, this is insane.

09:24.824 --> 09:27.325
Agreed. But traditions are traditions.

09:28.090 --> 09:29.493
Fine.

09:29.529 --> 09:30.728
I'll do it.

09:30.763 --> 09:33.731
Not like I've ever led
an army before, but...

09:33.766 --> 09:35.900
Well, I guess I could try.

09:35.935 --> 09:37.903
I suppose.

09:40.311 --> 09:41.939
I can guess the future.

09:42.066 --> 09:44.021
- We're screwed.
- Mm-hmm.

09:47.316 --> 09:48.649
[Knock on door]

09:49.785 --> 09:51.151
Gareth: There you are.

09:51.186 --> 09:52.819
I've been looking all over for ya.

09:52.854 --> 09:54.087
I'm packing for war.

09:55.179 --> 09:56.690
Yeah, well, after that, maybe,

09:56.725 --> 09:59.459
I thought we'd go and address the troops.

09:59.494 --> 10:02.395
Uh, why don't I put my
stuff in there with yours?

10:02.431 --> 10:03.563
I mean, I don't have a lot,

10:04.075 --> 10:06.709
and, uh, well, basically,
I wear this every day.

10:06.710 --> 10:07.842
Share a trunk?

10:08.677 --> 10:10.771
I don't want your stuff touching mine.

10:11.622 --> 10:12.539
Is everything okay?

10:12.540 --> 10:14.541
[Knock on door] Knock, knock!

10:14.576 --> 10:17.010
Gentle reminder... uh, I've
had a crow from the vicar.

10:17.045 --> 10:19.212
He'd love you to set a
date for the wedding soon,

10:19.213 --> 10:20.513
because he fills up in August.

10:20.549 --> 10:21.615
Inquisition season.

10:21.650 --> 10:23.350
Go! Shoo!

10:24.780 --> 10:25.552
[Door slams]

10:25.587 --> 10:27.988
God, he's just so...

10:28.023 --> 10:29.389
Ugh! [Laughs]

10:29.978 --> 10:30.557
You know?

10:31.135 --> 10:32.638
Well, actually,

10:32.840 --> 10:34.009
he <i> has</i> got a point.

10:34.010 --> 10:36.014
I mean, it's a bit confusing,

10:36.015 --> 10:40.000
you know, the king and queen not
actually being married, and...

10:40.035 --> 10:42.269
It was really nice when
you said that you loved me.

10:42.304 --> 10:45.272
Look, Gareth, let's not...

10:45.307 --> 10:47.274
Oh, my God! What are you doing?!

10:47.976 --> 10:49.409
[Grunts]

10:53.348 --> 10:55.282
I wasn't proposing!

10:55.317 --> 10:57.584
I was doing me boots up! Oy!

11:04.793 --> 11:06.459
Uh, hello. [Chuckles]

11:06.495 --> 11:07.461
Question.

11:07.578 --> 11:09.684
I was wondering if you had any scrolls

11:09.685 --> 11:12.183
that could help lead an army
against an attacking foe?

11:12.184 --> 11:14.680
Maybe something that could
help a person save the lives

11:14.681 --> 11:17.292
of everyone in Hortensia
from a certain slaughter?

11:19.847 --> 11:21.408
D... d... do you have any of those?

11:22.656 --> 11:24.044
Are you sure this is gonna work?

11:24.079 --> 11:26.146
'Cause if not, my career is kind of over...

11:26.181 --> 11:28.448
A squire killing his own knight and all.

11:28.483 --> 11:31.551
Good thing you've got your
priorities in the right place.

11:31.620 --> 11:32.686
Right.

11:32.721 --> 11:34.454
The moment of truth.

11:34.847 --> 11:36.085
It's ready.

11:36.236 --> 11:37.924
Isn't this exciting?

11:37.959 --> 11:40.293
- You do the honors.
- Oh, yeah.

11:40.329 --> 11:42.362
♪

11:44.000 --> 11:50.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

11:55.800 --> 11:56.676
Now what?

11:56.712 --> 11:58.212
We wait.

11:59.648 --> 12:02.448
Personally, I'm not a man who was
born with the gift of patience,

12:02.484 --> 12:05.552
so I choose to stay
distracted by decluttering.

12:06.645 --> 12:07.787
You're helping.

12:07.823 --> 12:09.289
Try not to stab me.

12:09.324 --> 12:13.174
Right. We will start in the
pantry and work our way down.

12:15.866 --> 12:17.130
Stay strong.

12:17.165 --> 12:18.498
It's funny.

12:18.533 --> 12:21.497
When you're king, you're
given everything you ever want.

12:22.732 --> 12:24.071
Now all I want is my friend back,

12:24.072 --> 12:25.905
and there's nothing I can do about it.

12:28.110 --> 12:29.243
[Hawk screeches]

12:29.244 --> 12:31.051
[Gasping]

12:35.851 --> 12:37.515
[Whoosh]

12:40.889 --> 12:42.322
Are...

12:42.357 --> 12:43.490
Are you death?

12:43.525 --> 12:46.226
[Bell tolls]

12:47.796 --> 12:49.095
I'm dead?

12:49.131 --> 12:51.898
[Bell tolls]

12:53.335 --> 12:55.602
[Bleep] Sid!

12:55.637 --> 12:57.704
[Whoosh]

12:57.739 --> 12:59.205
♪

13:04.746 --> 13:07.347
♪ Goodbye ♪

13:07.382 --> 13:10.950
♪ yes, it's time to say goodbye ♪

13:10.986 --> 13:15.054
♪ sad, I know, but, hey,
you're done with living ♪

13:15.090 --> 13:18.324
♪ it's time to give in and go ♪

13:18.360 --> 13:23.263
♪ and so, goodbye ♪

13:23.298 --> 13:27.066
♪ funny how the time did fly ♪

13:27.102 --> 13:28.701
♪ really, it's a crime ♪

13:28.737 --> 13:30.670
♪ you're heading forever ♪

13:30.705 --> 13:35.241
♪ to the great big
whatever in the sky ♪

13:35.277 --> 13:38.645
♪ don't bother packing,
simply say, "sayonara" ♪

13:38.680 --> 13:43.082
♪ 'cause there ain't no
tomorrow where you're going ♪

13:44.820 --> 13:46.753
♪ sure, we all feel for you ♪

13:46.788 --> 13:48.555
♪ but things just got real for you ♪

13:48.590 --> 13:53.126
♪ so why not make amends to
all your family and friends? ♪

13:56.097 --> 13:57.697
♪ Goodbye ♪

13:57.732 --> 13:58.731
Sid.

13:58.767 --> 14:02.836
- ♪ Sorry that I made you die ♪
- It's not okay, Sid.

14:02.871 --> 14:04.971
♪ Yeah, I'm here, I'm not sure why ♪

14:05.006 --> 14:06.606
Me, either. Seriously, who invited you?

14:06.641 --> 14:08.575
♪ Hold me 'cause I'm gonna cry ♪

14:08.610 --> 14:09.542
No.

14:09.578 --> 14:10.510
- ♪ My ♪
- Please.

14:10.545 --> 14:11.511
- ♪ Gal ♪
- Don't.

14:11.546 --> 14:13.413
- ♪ Pal ♪
- ♪ goodbye ♪

14:13.448 --> 14:14.380
Roberta.

14:14.416 --> 14:16.783
♪ Seems as though we just said hi ♪

14:16.818 --> 14:18.251
Yeah, well, we did. Who's this?

14:18.286 --> 14:21.254
♪ I am just some random guy ♪

14:21.289 --> 14:22.906
What happened? I just ran out of friends?

14:22.907 --> 14:23.690
Come.

14:23.725 --> 14:24.991
I'm not leaving. Not without...

14:25.026 --> 14:27.293
[Vocalizing] Isabella.

14:27.329 --> 14:29.062
But wait, is she in trouble?

14:29.097 --> 14:31.898
- [Gasps] Galavant?
- My love?

14:31.953 --> 14:34.754
- ♪ War has come, and with no gal here ♪
- ♪ I am with you ♪

14:34.790 --> 14:38.258
- ♪ beside me to support me and guide me ♪
- ♪ in spirit ♪

14:38.293 --> 14:40.927
- ♪ I could fail here ♪
- ♪ literally ♪

14:40.962 --> 14:44.331
♪ yet somehow, strangely,
I am sure I can do this ♪

14:44.366 --> 14:46.800
- ♪ yes, you can ♪
- ♪ sure, I'll somehow get through this ♪

14:46.835 --> 14:49.069
♪ and I sure don't need that jackass ♪

14:49.104 --> 14:51.677
- ♪ who completely broke my heart ♪
- Wait, what?

14:51.678 --> 14:53.077
♪ And like he said to me ♪

14:53.078 --> 14:55.008
♪ that schmuck can go die in a fart ♪

14:55.043 --> 14:57.313
I didn't say that. I've never
made a fart joke in my life.

14:57.314 --> 14:58.478
You asked to see me, princess?

14:58.513 --> 15:00.113
Take me to the armory.

15:00.148 --> 15:01.997
It's time to defend this kingdom.

15:02.229 --> 15:03.210
Wait.

15:03.211 --> 15:04.951
No, Izzy, there's been a misunderstanding.

15:04.976 --> 15:05.952
♪ Goodbye ♪

15:05.987 --> 15:06.953
Stop singing!

15:06.988 --> 15:08.922
♪ Now it's time to say goodbye ♪

15:08.957 --> 15:10.557
No. I have to go back.

15:10.592 --> 15:12.192
♪ Wish that you could stay ♪

15:12.227 --> 15:14.494
♪ you can't, though,
and we both know why ♪

15:14.529 --> 15:15.829
No, I have to tell her...

15:15.864 --> 15:18.131
♪ Now your big finish is nigh ♪

15:18.166 --> 15:19.599
No, she has to know that I love her.

15:19.634 --> 15:22.335
♪ Time to look death in the eye ♪

15:22.371 --> 15:25.238
♪ and sa-a-a-a-y ♪

15:26.942 --> 15:28.108
- [Crunch!]
- [Groans]

15:28.503 --> 15:30.303
[Wheezes] Goodbye.

15:30.338 --> 15:33.272
[Screaming] Why do I still have these?

15:33.308 --> 15:34.841
No, I'm all right! Leave me alone!

15:34.876 --> 15:37.510
Oh, shut up!

15:39.919 --> 15:40.952
[Sighs]

15:42.717 --> 15:44.817
Perhaps it's time to let him go.

15:45.971 --> 15:47.020
No.

15:48.006 --> 15:49.139
I'm not ready.

15:50.591 --> 15:51.891
You must.

15:52.326 --> 15:54.226
He's all I have.

15:54.261 --> 15:56.864
That's not true.

15:56.865 --> 15:58.131
You've got me.

16:00.626 --> 16:01.625
I do?

16:03.037 --> 16:04.670
Richard, you're the reason

16:04.705 --> 16:06.839
I came on this journey to begin with.

16:06.874 --> 16:08.908
It's always been you.

16:09.342 --> 16:13.420
I guess what I'm trying to say
is when all's said and done...

16:13.421 --> 16:17.657
I'm just a girl standing in front of a boy

16:18.143 --> 16:23.022
over a dead body, asking him to like her.

16:23.057 --> 16:25.124
[Exhales sharply]

16:25.159 --> 16:28.159
♪

16:31.299 --> 16:33.099
[Gasps]

16:33.134 --> 16:35.635
[Groaning]

16:35.657 --> 16:37.624
Welcome back, old friend! Mwah!

16:37.972 --> 16:38.938
[Laughs]

16:38.973 --> 16:40.606
- Isn't this terrific?
- Yeah.

16:40.641 --> 16:42.108
You couldn't wait 30 more seconds

16:42.143 --> 16:43.476
to come back from the dead, huh?

16:47.662 --> 16:50.863
Scratch that trunk, and you'll
be in pieces in the next trunk.

16:53.420 --> 16:54.300
Listen...

16:55.683 --> 16:57.890
We should talk about
this whole wedding thing.

16:57.891 --> 17:00.944
What? Talk? Since when do we talk?

17:01.242 --> 17:03.042
Your Highness...

17:03.497 --> 17:05.305
Your troops are ready for review.

17:05.306 --> 17:06.683
Oh, thank God.

17:06.684 --> 17:10.521
Look, Gareth, I can't talk
about these kinds of things.

17:10.521 --> 17:11.595
I'm sorry.

17:12.337 --> 17:13.509
Let's drop it.

17:20.096 --> 17:21.596
Come on, Queenie.

17:21.729 --> 17:25.013
When we started this, we said
we'd never go to war angry.

17:25.015 --> 17:25.865
I'm not angry.

17:25.900 --> 17:27.700
I just don't want to discuss it with you.

17:28.260 --> 17:29.034
Okay, then.

17:29.070 --> 17:31.704
We'll discuss it with someone else.

17:31.739 --> 17:34.006
Soldiers of Valencia!

17:34.399 --> 17:35.365
I love you!

17:35.877 --> 17:37.146
There it is!

17:37.543 --> 17:38.531
It's out in the open!

17:38.532 --> 17:40.312
I said it for the first time in my life!

17:40.982 --> 17:42.395
What do you think about that?

17:42.396 --> 17:44.287
All: We love you, too, sir.

17:46.386 --> 17:49.637
And I appreciate that... Soldiers.

17:50.450 --> 17:54.326
And, yes, I too am starting
to feel the same way.

17:55.026 --> 17:56.962
But this is all new to me, you know?

17:57.319 --> 17:58.887
I've never felt this way before,

17:58.888 --> 18:01.901
and now there's this pressure to
move forward, forward, forward!

18:04.471 --> 18:07.606
It's important that you
feel comfortable, soldiers.

18:08.439 --> 18:11.510
So maybe we should slow down a bit.

18:11.545 --> 18:13.479
We got something special,

18:14.108 --> 18:16.342
and I don't want to ruin it.

18:19.360 --> 18:20.693
That's good to hear.

18:23.012 --> 18:25.591
At least, I imagine it is.

18:25.626 --> 18:26.825
For the soldiers.

18:29.367 --> 18:31.100
Who wants to go to war?!

18:31.332 --> 18:32.598
[Cheering]

18:35.603 --> 18:37.102
Yeah!

18:40.685 --> 18:42.941
Hmm, whoop-de-do.

18:42.977 --> 18:45.978
It's party time.

18:50.384 --> 18:53.685
I need all maps, time
tables, previous battle plans,

18:53.721 --> 18:56.688
and a glass of milk, because
I have a really stress-y tummy.

18:56.724 --> 18:58.690
Guards, open the armory.

18:58.726 --> 19:01.393
Show me Hortensia's weapons of war.

19:01.428 --> 19:03.695
♪

19:20.039 --> 19:20.946
This is it?

19:20.981 --> 19:22.147
These are all toys!

19:22.390 --> 19:23.390
Yeah.

19:23.517 --> 19:25.484
Maybe it wasn't the best idea

19:25.519 --> 19:28.420
to put an 11-year-old in
charge of designing the army.

19:29.967 --> 19:31.623
Mmm.

19:32.660 --> 19:34.326
Chocolate.

19:37.585 --> 19:39.132
[Chuckles]

19:39.998 --> 19:41.496
Did something happen between you two?

19:41.497 --> 19:42.894
'Cause you're kind of creeping me out.

19:42.895 --> 19:44.069
- No.
- No.

19:44.364 --> 19:47.125
- Well, I've really enjoyed spending some time with you.
- Mm-hmm.

19:47.126 --> 19:49.013
- See you again, I hope.
- Yeah. Yeah, sure.

19:49.014 --> 19:49.761
We good to go?

19:49.762 --> 19:51.343
Hortensia's still a few days...

19:51.378 --> 19:52.477
[hacking]

19:53.632 --> 19:54.713
Ugh, sorry.

19:54.748 --> 19:56.048
I feel like there's a very tiny,

19:56.083 --> 19:57.983
wiry little hair stuck
in the back of my throat.

19:58.719 --> 19:59.818
- Weird.
- Yeah.

19:59.853 --> 20:01.186
Huh. You were saying?

20:01.221 --> 20:03.756
We must come to Isabella's aid,
whether we have an army or no.

20:03.757 --> 20:04.954
Army?

20:05.059 --> 20:06.921
You know, if you're looking for an army,

20:06.922 --> 20:10.829
I have something here that
might be of interest to you.

20:10.864 --> 20:13.864
♪

20:15.963 --> 20:19.872
There was a war here a few years back.

20:21.408 --> 20:24.876
And I've been using the
dead and buried soldiers

20:24.912 --> 20:26.011
to experiment on.

20:27.713 --> 20:28.846
With a bit of success.

20:29.767 --> 20:32.651
You've got a freaky side, Neo,

20:33.160 --> 20:34.653
but I like it.

20:34.688 --> 20:36.655
There's a few hundred of them back there,

20:36.690 --> 20:39.591
which makes them an
army... Half-dead army.

20:39.626 --> 20:40.859
Or half-alive.

20:40.894 --> 20:43.195
Depends on whether you're a
glass-half-dead kind of guy.

20:43.230 --> 20:45.530
Either way, they're yours if you want them.

20:46.433 --> 20:48.734
Please take them. They freak me out.

20:48.769 --> 20:50.102
I like it.

20:50.137 --> 20:51.636
[Soldiers growling] Back, back!

20:53.089 --> 20:56.041
Have to be careful. They're... a bit bitey.

20:56.076 --> 20:57.676
[Growling continues]

